Estimate tree height and crown dimensions

Author

Vincyane Badouard

Published

February 20, 2025

Arbres communs avec ceux de Claudia -> prendre lâestimation de Claudia de la hauteur de lâarbre et du rayon de la couronne
Autres arbres :
- TreeHeight : par une allomÃ©trie issue des donnÃ©es de Claudia et FTH
- CrownDiameter : par une allomÃ©trie CC (Ã  faire en dernier)

Pour tout le monde :
- CrownHeight = TreeHeight * 0.3

PRENDRE DBHcor !!!!
Sauf pour les multistems : il faut prendre DBH de la 1Ã¨re tige

Plot crown dimensions data

Code 
data %>%
  mutate(CrownHeight = TreeHeight*0.3) %>% 
  ggplot() +
  aes(x = DBH, y = CrownHeight) +
  # Estimated height
  geom_point(aes(col = "Crown height estimated"), size = 0.2) + 
  geom_smooth(span = 0.75, linewidth = 0.8, aes(color = "Crown height estimated")) +
  # Measured height
  geom_point(size = 0.2, aes(TreeHeight - CrownBase, col = "Crown height measured")) +
  geom_smooth(span = 0.75, linewidth = 0.8, aes(TreeHeight - CrownBase, col = "Crown height measured")) +
  # Measured diameter
  geom_point(size = 0.2, aes(y = CrownRadius*2, color = "Crown diameter estimated")) + 
  geom_smooth(span = 0.75, linewidth = 0.8, aes(y = CrownRadius*2, color = "Crown diameter estimated")) + # using method = 'gam' and formula 'y ~ s(x, bs = "cs")'
  
  theme_minimal() +
  scale_color_manual(values = c("Crown height estimated" = "#CC79A7",
                                "Crown height measured" = "#00AFBB",
                                "Crown diameter estimated"= "#E7B800")) +
  labs(title = "Canopy Constructor & FTH data - crown dimensions", x ="DBH (cm)", y = "Crown dimension (m)") +
  scale_x_continuous(limits = c(0, 150), breaks = seq(0, 150, by=10)) +
  theme(legend.position="bottom",
        # axis.title= element_text(size=16), axis.text= element_text(size=16), legend.text= element_text(size=16),
        legend.title= element_blank() 
  )

Claudiaâs trees

Code 
Adults <- Adults %>% 
  left_join((CC %>% select(-DBH)), by="idTree") %>% # + TreeHeight, CrownRadius
      left_join((FTH %>% select(-c(DBH, Family, ScientificName))), by=c("TreeFieldNum", "SubPlot")) %>% 
  mutate( # mutate sur plusieurs variables
    idTree = coalesce(idTree.x, idTree.y), # pour combiner les valeurs de .x et .y prioritÃ© Ã  .x (cc better than FTH for >10dbh)
    TreeHeight = coalesce(TreeHeight.x, TreeHeight.y),
    CrownRadius = coalesce(CrownRadius.x, CrownRadius.y),
    HeightHow = coalesce(HeightHow.x, HeightHow.y)
  ) %>% 
  select(-(contains(".x") | contains(".y"))) # 6931

Other trees

Fits and compares height-diameter models (BIOMASS)

toutes espÃ¨ces confondues #### For DBH >= 10 cm

Code 
ModelsresultGuiana <- modelHD( # fits and compares (optional) height-diameter models
  D = data$DBH,
  H = data$TreeHeight,
  useWeight = F
)
Code 
knitr::kable(ModelsresultGuiana)
method color RSE RSElog Average_bias
log1 blue 4.661391 0.1753944 0.0207104
log2 green 2.792222 0.1214638 0.0008841
weibull orange 2.797694 NA 0.0007105
michaelis purple 2.796711 NA 0.0006911
Code 
# the lowest RSE: log2 (RSE= 2.792), michaelis :    2.796711

HDmodelGuiana <- modelHD(
  D = data$DBH,
  H = data$TreeHeight,
  method = "michaelis", # Compute the H-D model with the lowest RSE.
  useWeight = F # T = larger trees have a stronger influence during the construction of the model 
)
HDmodelGuiana$coefficients
  Estimate Std. Error  t value Pr(>|t|)
A 48.87652  0.1526790 320.1261        0
B 18.59470  0.1285109 144.6936        0
Code 
# log2 : exp(0.6988852 + 1.1989242*log(DBH) + -0.1187707*log(DBH)^2)
# michaelis : (48.87652 * DBH)/(18.59470 + DBH) *exp(error)

EstimA <- Adults %>%
  filter(is.na(TreeHeight)) %>% # 24 trees
  mutate(TreeHeight = ifelse(Multistem==T, retrieveH(D= Diameter, model = HDmodelGuiana)$H, # Diameter -> DBH
                             retrieveH(D= DBHcor, model = HDmodelGuiana)$H)) %>% 
  mutate(HeightHow = "Local allometry")

Adults <- Adults %>%
  filter(!is.na(TreeHeight)) %>% 
  bind_rows(EstimA) %>% 
  mutate(CrownHeight = TreeHeight*0.3)

HDmodelGuiana <- modelHD(
  D = FTH$DBH,
  H = FTH$TreeHeight,

  useWeight = F # T = larger trees have a stronger influence during the construction of the model 
)

EstimU <- Understory %>% # 28 711
  filter(is.na(TreeHeight)) %>% # 28 045 trees
  mutate(TreeHeight = ifelse(Multistem==T, retrieveH(D= DBH, model = HDmodelGuiana)$H,
                             retrieveH(D= DBHcor, model = HDmodelGuiana)$H)) %>% 
  mutate(HeightHow = "Local allometry")

Understory <- Understory %>%
  filter(!is.na(TreeHeight)) %>% 
  bind_rows(EstimU) %>% 
  mutate(CrownHeight = TreeHeight*0.3)

Estimate CrownRadius

Pour estimer le rayon de la couronne des arbres absents des donnÃ©es de Claudia, je dois utiliser lâallomÃ©trie de CanopyConstructor dont je ne connais pas la valeur des paramÃ¨tres. Donc je dois les estimer Ã  partir des donnÃ©es de Claudia pour les arbres >10 cm.

Pour les arbres >=10 cm, on fitte lâallomÃ©trie sur les donnÃ©es de Claudia et FTH
Pour les arbres <10 cm, on fitte lâallomÃ©trie que sur les donnÃ©es FTH (vaut mieux surestimer la couronne pour Ã©viter lâauto-ombrage)

For DBH >= 10 cm

Code 
# La relation allomÃ©trique de CanopyConstructor : exp(alpha + epsilon) * DBH^beta

# ModÃ¨le linÃ©aire pour estimation initiale
lm_fit <- lm(log(data$CrownRadius) ~ log(data$DBH), data = data)

# Estimations initiales
alpha_init <- coef(lm_fit)[1] # -0.815
beta_init <- coef(lm_fit)[2] # 0.629

# Ajustement avec nls (Nonlinear Least Squares)
nls_fit <- nls(CrownRadius ~ exp(alpha) * (DBH^beta),
               data = data,
               start = list(alpha = alpha_init, beta = beta_init))

# RÃ©cupÃ©rer les paramÃ¨tres estimÃ©s
coef <- coef(nls_fit)

# Estimation
EstimA <- Adults %>%
  filter(is.na(CrownRadius)) %>% # 24 trees
  mutate(CrownRadius = ifelse(Multistem==T, exp(coef["alpha"] + coef["beta"] * log(Diameter)), # Diameter -> DBH
                              exp(coef["alpha"] + coef["beta"] * log(DBHcor))))

Adults <- Adults %>%
  filter(!is.na(CrownRadius)) %>% 
  bind_rows(EstimA)

CC <- CC %>% 
  mutate(CrownRadius_est = exp(coef["alpha"]) * (DBH^coef["beta"]))
